A man has been arrested for attempting to steal a spare wheel of a car parked outside the Directorate of Criminal Investigations headquarters on Kiambu Road. Wilson Muinde 35, who is from Utawala in Nairobi is expected in court on Wednesday, DCI boss George Kinoti said via Twitter. The DCI has made several arrests countrywide in a bid to bring law and order. On October 25 Last year, DCI detectives arrested five suspects Emmaculate Njeri, Johnson Gichobi, Joseph Mwangi, Samuel Mwangi, and Samuel Wachira on charges of stealing two vehicles. The DCI said the vehicles that had been reported stolen, were recovered at Chaka. More on this: Five arrested as DCI recovers two stolen vehicles in Chaka